{
  "texts": [
    "For G-PCC, the advantage of P2 over P1 and P3 is mainly present at R1 and R2, while all configurations achieve very similar JOD values at R4.",
    "On the other hand, P3 is only the best-performing configuration for Soldier.",
    "These plots suggest that a potential improvement in performance can be achieved in relation to the CTC parameters.",
    "However, the measured improvement is not high, going over 1 JOD only for Soldier at R1.",
    "Moreover, the results of this study only suggest the existence of better rate allocation methods for G-PCC without proposing an optimal scheme."
  ]
}